lyze/expressions/ExpressionAnalyzer.java", "diffHunk": "@@ -676,6 +642,15 @@ protected Symbol visitSubscriptExpression(SubscriptExpression node, ExpressionAn\n                 Symbol index = node.index().accept(this, context);\n                 return allocateFunction(SubscriptFunction.NAME, List.of(base, index), context);\n             } else {\n+                // Detect and process partial quoted subscript expression\n+                var nameParts = qualifiedName.getParts();\n+                var columnName = nameParts.get(nameParts.size() - 1);", "originalCommit": "fa4e728a8a8b243fa34b3cd5e87f69f53b66c67d", "replyToReviewId": null, "replies": null, "type": "inlineReview"}, {"oid": "7bf9710a4f5ffa1f9af41768da137ba2e5ead845", "url": "https://github.com/crate/crate/commit/7bf9710a4f5ffa1f9af41768da137ba2e5ead845", "message": "Always allow and support quoted subscript expressions\n\nAdd full support for quoted subscript expressions by default.\nPartial quoted subscript expressions will work as well.\n\nThis adds out-of-the-box support for various clients which do not know\nCrateDB\u2019s special subscript expression (and also don\u2019t make use of the\nserver-side `quote_ident` function) and thus always quote the full\nqualified column name.\nInner columns (schema) of object data types are exposed by system\ninformational tables at ``information_schema``, ``sys`` and ``pg_catalog``\nschemas and thus used by clients.\n\nRelates #10163.", "committedDate": "2020-09-03T13:57:30Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "a752ce604dc9d9805394e867fb5c447cdb5f1264", "url": "https://github.com/crate/crate/commit/a752ce604dc9d9805394e867fb5c447cdb5f1264", "message": "Remove obsolete ALLOW_QUOTED_SUBSCRIPT session option\n\nQuoted subscript expressions are always support now. Also this setting\nwas never exposed.", "committedDate": "2020-09-03T13:57:30Z", "type": "commit"}, {"oid": "a752ce604dc9d9805394e867fb5c447cdb5f1264", "url": "https://github.com/crate/crate/commit/a752ce604dc9d980